The government should develop a standard list of prices for public procurement to eliminate corruption in tendering. That’s according to Victor Ogalo, policy research and analysis manager of the Kenya Private Sector Alliance He said on Thursday Kepsa is concerned about graft in national and county procurement. Ogalo was addressing the press during the launch of Business Ethics and Integrity Training workshop at a hotel in Machakos county. “It is unbelievable that a pen can be bought at Sh100 in government procurement,” Ogalo said.